# OBSERVABILITY.md — AI-Specific Observability Schema

ADLC P6 artifact. **Schema and alert-rule config** only — not live data. Adopter project owns the actual telemetry stack (OpenLLMetry / Helicone / custom). This file is the *contract* of what gets measured.

Generated/maintained via `/ai-observe` skill.

---

## Metrics (per feature)

### Behavioral
| Metric | Definition | Source | Sample rate | Alert threshold |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Hallucination rate | [definition] | [eval-judge call / RAG faithfulness / domain-specific] | [1.0 / 0.1 sample] | [threshold] |
| Output-distribution drift | [statistical test] | [baseline vs. current window] | [window size] | [threshold] |
| Toxicity | [definition] | [content-mod API / LLM judge] | [rate] | [threshold] |
| Tool-call success rate | [definition] | [orchestrator logs] | [rate] | [threshold] |

### Operational
| Metric | Definition | Source | Sample rate | Alert threshold |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Latency p50/p95/p99 | [definition] | [tracing] | [rate] | [threshold] |
| Cost per task | $ tokens + tool-calls | [billing] | [rate] | [threshold] |
| Escalation rate | % tasks routed to human | [agent runtime] | [rate] | [threshold] |
| Confidence-on-low-quality | avg confidence when output later flagged | [eval pipeline] | [rate] | [threshold] |

### Drift signals
| Metric | Triggers | Action |
|---|---|---|
| Input distribution shift | [test result above threshold] | Schedule `/drift-audit` |
| Eval delta | [metric] moves > tolerance from baseline | Open ticket; consider golden-dataset refresh |
| Model-provider notification | Provider blog post / changelog entry | Schedule MG gate run |

